The paper discusses the development of a new method for optimal design of experiments for model discrimination using Gaussian process surrogates. This involves machine learning techniques such as approximate inference and black-box models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of statistical methods such as the Jensen-Renyi divergence and model uncertainty, which suggests sub-categories such as cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as possible options.
